âœ… Definition

CopyOnWriteArrayList is a thread-safe List implementation where all mutative operations (add, remove, update) create a new copy of the underlying array, allowing lock-free and consistent reads.

ğŸ”¹ Key Characteristics

âœ” Thread-safe
âœ” Read operations are lock-free
âœ” Write operations are synchronized (locked)
âœ” No ConcurrentModificationException
âœ” Best for read-heavy scenarios

ğŸ”¥ Interview Line

CopyOnWriteArrayList achieves thread safety by copying the array on writes and allowing lock-free reads on immutable snapshots.

2ï¸âƒ£ CopyOnWriteArraySet
âœ… Definition

CopyOnWriteArraySet is a thread-safe Set implementation backed by a CopyOnWriteArrayList, ensuring no duplicates and providing lock-free read operations.

ğŸ”¹ Key Characteristics

âœ” Thread-safe
âœ” No duplicates
âœ” Lock-free reads
âœ” Slower writes
âœ” Maintains insertion order


ğŸ”¥ Interview Line
CopyOnWriteArraySet provides thread-safe uniqueness by delegating storage to CopyOnWriteArrayList and using snapshot-based reads.

